{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "/second-brain-wiki Ingest this Slack thread into my wiki:\n\nChannel: #uxd-rhoai\nThread started by Andy Braren, 2026-07-02\n\nAndy: Hey team, quick update on the AI helpers repo strategy. We're going\nwith a centralized repo that distributes skills via MRs to consuming projects.\nEach skill gets its own directory with a SKILL.md and references folder.\n\nEvan: nice, does that mean we can version skills independently?\n\nAndy: Exactly. Each skill directory is self-contained. Teams pull what they\nneed. We'll have a review process for new skills going in.\n\nZack: What about testing? Do we require eval configs for every skill?\n\nAndy: Good question. Starting with recommended-but-optional. Once we have\nenough examples of good eval.yaml configs, we'll make it required.\n\nEvan: makes sense. the agent-eval-harness pattern would work well for that\n\nAndy: Yep, that's the plan. I'll send a more detailed proposal next week."}, "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:58:06.361Z"}
