{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FNACTinufFhUhtjsxqUyHG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Agent Eval Harness\n2\t\n3\tA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n4\t\n5\t## How It Works\n6\t\n7\t1. **eval.yaml** — defines execution mode, dataset schema, output descriptions, judges, models, and thresholds\n8\t2. **Dataset** — test cases with realistic inputs for the skill\n9\t3. **Judges** — automated scorers that rate skill outputs against criteria\n10\t4. **Run** — executes the skill against test cases, scores with judges, reports results\n11\t5. **Optimize** — identifies failures, edits SKILL.md, re-runs to verify, checks for regressions\n12\t\n13\t## Key Skills (from the harness)\n14\t\n15\t- `/eval-analyze` — examine a skill and generate eval.yaml\n16\t- `/eval-dataset` — generate test cases for a skill\n17\t- `/eval-run` — execute evaluation against test cases\n18\t- `/eval-optimize` — automated improvement loop\n19\t- `/eval-review` — interactive human review of results\n20\t\n21\t## The Optimize Loop\n22\t\n23\t```\n24\tRun eval → Identify judge failures → Read traces → Edit SKILL.md → Re-run → Verify\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\tThis is directly applicable to the [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) work — the same pattern of rubric-based scoring, automated iteration, and quality gates.\n28\t\n29\t## MLflow Integration\n30\t\n31\tResults can be logged to MLflow for tracking, dataset syncing, and trace-level feedback.\n32\t\n33\t## Related\n34\t\n35\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — uses rubric-based scoring for prototypes\n36\t- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — the 4-dimension scoring system\n37\t- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — includes run-evals skill\n38\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — applies eval patterns to prototype evaluation\n39\t- [Red Hat AI-First Lessons](redhat-ai-first-lessons.md) — Jeremy Eder's presentation referencing EvalHub, Harbor, MLflow, and the harness\n40\t- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — eval patterns relevant to measuring heuristic eval pilot results\n41\t- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n42\t- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — judge prompts and SKILL.md are prompt engineering artifacts; format specs and CoT improve scoring reliability\n43\t- [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs\n44\t\n45\t## Sources\n46\t\n47\t- sources/2026-06-04-agent-eval-harness-overview.html\n48\t- opendatahub-io agent-eval-harness skills (installed as plugins)\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8e66553-f21b-4f03-bfa0-c0038adb359b","uuid":"3d4c2b29-b7d2-41e8-add8-e19dc026324c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:58:26.897Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/agent-eval-harness.md","content":"# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **eval.yaml** — defines execution mode, dataset schema, output descriptions, judges, models, and thresholds\n2. **Dataset** — test cases with realistic inputs for the skill\n3. **Judges** — automated scorers that rate skill outputs against criteria\n4. **Run** — executes the skill against test cases, scores with judges, reports results\n5. **Optimize** — identifies failures, edits SKILL.md, re-runs to verify, checks for regressions\n\n## Key Skills (from the harness)\n\n- `/eval-analyze` — examine a skill and generate eval.yaml\n- `/eval-dataset` — generate test cases for a skill\n- `/eval-run` — execute evaluation against test cases\n- `/eval-optimize` — automated improvement loop\n- `/eval-review` — interactive human review of results\n\n## The Optimize Loop\n\n```\nRun eval → Identify judge failures → Read traces → Edit SKILL.md → Re-run → Verify\n```\n\nThis is directly applicable to the [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) work — the same pattern of rubric-based scoring, automated iteration, and quality gates.\n\n## MLflow Integration\n\nResults can be logged to MLflow for tracking, dataset syncing, and trace-level feedback.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — uses rubric-based scoring for prototypes\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — the 4-dimension scoring system\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — includes run-evals skill\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — applies eval patterns to prototype evaluation\n- [Red Hat AI-First Lessons](redhat-ai-first-lessons.md) — Jeremy Eder's presentation referencing EvalHub, Harbor, MLflow, and the harness\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — eval patterns relevant to measuring heuristic eval pilot results\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — judge prompts and SKILL.md are prompt engineering artifacts; format specs and CoT improve scoring reliability\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/2026-06-04-agent-eval-harness-overview.html\n- opendatahub-io agent-eval-harness skills (installed as plugins)\n","numLines":49,"startLine":1,"totalLines":49}}}
