{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01HvqQmVzgnweHGbb5Sqj2Jk", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01B4Wefk2em95P1KbgdAyskz", "name": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md", "content": "# Source: #uxd-rhoai Slack Thread \u2014 2026-07-02\n\nChannel: #uxd-rhoai\nThread started by Andy Braren, 2026-07-02\n\nAndy: Hey team, quick update on the AI helpers repo strategy. We're going\nwith a centralized repo that distributes skills via MRs to consuming projects.\nEach skill gets its own directory with a SKILL.md and references folder.\n\nEvan: nice, does that mean we can version skills independently?\n\nAndy: Exactly. Each skill directory is self-contained. Teams pull what they\nneed. We'll have a review process for new skills going in.\n\nZack: What about testing? Do we require eval configs for every skill?\n\nAndy: Good question. Starting with recommended-but-optional. Once we have\nenough examples of good eval.yaml configs, we'll make it required.\n\nEvan: makes sense. the agent-eval-harness pattern would work well for that\n\nAndy: Yep, that's the plan. I'll send a more detailed proposal next week.\n"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4425, "cache_read_input_tokens": 37315, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4425, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "a8e66553-f21b-4f03-bfa0-c0038adb359b", "uuid": "c4186ffd-07a5-43e4-b1bf-e5456cf83848", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011Ccrm2L1YMzZ1wHJSbn7LN", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:58:53.729Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01B4Wefk2em95P1KbgdAyskz","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8e66553-f21b-4f03-bfa0-c0038adb359b","uuid":"a2ca14c7-8464-4f4d-8637-bb16581a4479","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:58:53.739Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md","content":"# Source: #uxd-rhoai Slack Thread — 2026-07-02\n\nChannel: #uxd-rhoai\nThread started by Andy Braren, 2026-07-02\n\nAndy: Hey team, quick update on the AI helpers repo strategy. We're going\nwith a centralized repo that distributes skills via MRs to consuming projects.\nEach skill gets its own directory with a SKILL.md and references folder.\n\nEvan: nice, does that mean we can version skills independently?\n\nAndy: Exactly. Each skill directory is self-contained. Teams pull what they\nneed. We'll have a review process for new skills going in.\n\nZack: What about testing? Do we require eval configs for every skill?\n\nAndy: Good question. Starting with recommended-but-optional. Once we have\nenough examples of good eval.yaml configs, we'll make it required.\n\nEvan: makes sense. the agent-eval-harness pattern would work well for that\n\nAndy: Yep, that's the plan. I'll send a more detailed proposal next week.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01RFHGMaSFkVBHvrZPJ9sikW", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01M7oHEPgxHs5CpsKr5ME3nM", "name": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/ai-helpers-repo-slack-2026-07-02.md", "content": "# AI Helpers Repo Strategy Update \u2014 2026-07-02\n\nAndy Braren's #uxd-rhoai Slack update confirming skill directory structure, independent versioning, and eval config policy for the centralized AI helpers repo.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Centralized repo distributes skills to consuming projects via merge requests (MRs), not ad-hoc downloads\n- Each skill lives in its own directory with a `SKILL.md` and a `references/` folder \u2014 fully self-contained\n- Teams pull only the skills they need; independent versioning per skill directory\n- Review process required for all new skills entering the repo\n- Eval configs (`eval.yaml`) are **recommended-but-optional** now; will become **required** once enough good examples exist\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) pattern identified as the right testing approach for skills\n- Andy plans to send a more detailed proposal the following week (2026-07-08)\n\n## Related\n\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy \u2014 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) \u2014 the earlier strategy meeting that established centralized repo distribution; this thread is a follow-up confirmation\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) \u2014 the eval framework called out as the testing pattern for skills\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency \u2014 2026-06-29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) \u2014 AI helpers repo as primary vetted skills source, discussed the week before this thread\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) \u2014 example of a personal skills workspace that follows the self-contained skill directory pattern\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1670, "cache_read_input_tokens": 41740, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1670, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 21}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "a8e66553-f21b-4f03-bfa0-c0038adb359b", "uuid": "93fb3b15-2f45-4620-a8f6-57ff3cb987c2", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011Ccrm4JqABYRGMc7SgqeD3", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:59:02.697Z"}
